("544","1","2022-03-25 12:23:00","2022-03-25 12:23:00","<h6>Responsibilities</h6p>\r\n<ul>\r\n	<li>Work with the Navikenz Data Scientist team to implement the most appropriate techniques for model selection and development for problems to be solved\r\n</li>\r\n	<li>Build algorithms and design experiments to merge, manage, interrogate and extract data to supply tailored reports to colleagues, customers or the wider organization</li>\r\n	<li>Test AI/ML models to select the most appropriate ones for use on a project</li>\r\n	<li>Work with the team on data sourcing and/or developing data pipeline for the solutions</li>\r\n	<li>Work on the data analysis and exploration work with visualization tools \r\n</li>\r\n	<li>Build clear reports that tell compelling stories about the insights learned from data and the proposed actions/strategies/options as a result</li>\r\n	<li>Assist the team on the model to make it scalable, maintainable and production-ready\r\n</li>\r\n	<li>Stay up to date with the latest technology, techniques and methods\r\n</li>\r\n	<li>Conduct research from which you\'ll develop prototypes and proof of concepts</li>\r\n	<li>Manage/maintain the repository of built ML models and monitor for opportunities to use built insights/datasets/code/models for other clients</li>\r\n	<li>Stay curious and enthusiastic about using algorithms to solve problems and enthuse others to see the benefit of your work</li>\r\n\r\n</ul>\r\n\r\n<h6>Qualifications/Experience</h6>\r\n<p>The ideal candidate will have a Bachelor’s, Master’s Degree in Statistics, Mathematics, Computer Science or another quantitative field, with around 2 years of professional experience working on data sets and building statistical models, and familiar with the following software/tools/techniques:</p>\r\n","Software Developer – ML/AI","","inherit","closed","closed","","307-revision-v1","","","2022-03-25 12:23:00","2022-03-25 12:23:00","","307","http://projects.lollypop.design/navikenz-wp/?p=544","0","revision","","0"),
